cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category deals with optimization problems and the proposed bi-objective ranking scheme can be seen as a type of optimization. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category deals with the design and analysis of algorithms, which is the main focus of the paper. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the use of statistical methods to analyze data, which is relevant to the proposed ranking scheme. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): This sub-category deals with the use of computational methods to solve problems in various fields, which is relevant to the application of the proposed ranking scheme to solve benchmark problems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category deals with the development of intelligent algorithms, which is relevant to the comparison of different heuristics in the paper.
